50|$|Mothetjoa Metsing is a Lesotho {{politician}} {{who has been}} Deputy Prime Minister <b>of</b> <b>Lesotho</b> since June 2012. He is a member <b>of</b> the <b>Lesotho</b> Congress for Democracy (LCD) and serves in the <b>government</b> <b>of</b> Prime Minister Tom Thabane. In 2014, {{he was involved in}} controversy over an alleged coup attempt against the prime minister that was eventually resolved over calls for an early election.|$|R
